cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper proposes a deep neural network for visual odometry and localization, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The use of recurrent convolutional neural networks (RCNNs) and cross transformation constraints (CTC) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of drift in long-term navigation, which is relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
